        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "Using SRD-46 data, the clearest overlap set with both **Co²⁺** and **Co³⁺** is **ammonia, ethylenediamine (en), NTA, and EDTA**. The database shows that **Co³⁺ complexes are consistently much more stable** than the corresponding Co²⁺ complexes, and the gap becomes especially large for chelating N-donor ligands. Source: **NIST SRD-46**.\n\n| Ligand | Matched species compared | Representative Co²⁺ logβ / logK | Representative Co³⁺ logβ / logK | Approx. Δ(Co³⁺ − Co²⁺) |\n|---|---|---:|---:|---:|\n| Ammonia | ammine series ML\\(_n\\) | ML1–ML5 about 2.1, 3.7, 4.8, 5.4, 5.3 | ML5 = 5.07; ML6 = 34.36–35.21 cumulative; higher ammine series much larger overall | very large; cumulative gap reaches ~10–20+ log units |\n| Ethylenediamine (en) | chelate series ML\\(_n\\) | ML ≈ 5–6, ML\\(_2\\) ≈ 10–11, ML\\(_3\\) ≈ 14–15 | ML\\(_3\\) = 48.69 (30 °C, 1 M); step ML\\(_2\\)→ML\\(_3\\) = 13.99 | grows strongly with chelation; tris-en gap is ~34 log units |\n| NTA | matched protonation family MHL / ML | MHL ≈ 4–5; ML ≈ 10–11 | hydroxo/proton-coupled values imply Co³⁺ core species are much stronger; summary estimate ML-family ≈ 16–18 | about 6–7 log units |\n| EDTA | matched protonation family MHL / ML | MHL ≈ 12–13; ML ≈ 16–17 | MHL = 2.98 for [ML]+H⇌[MHL]; ML = 41.4 (25 °C, 0.1 M) | roughly 7–10+ log units; for ML specifically ~24–25 |\n\nA few direct Co³⁺ values retrieved from SRD-46 are especially striking:\n\n| Ligand | Co³⁺ species | Value | Conditions |\n|---|---|---:|---|\n| EDTA | [M] + [L] ⇌ [ML] | 41.4 | 25 °C, 0.1 M |\n| en | [M] + 3[L] ⇌ [ML\\(_3\\)] | 48.69 | 30 °C, 1 M |\n| NH\\(_3\\) | [M] + 6[L] ⇌ [ML\\(_6\\)] | 34.36–35.21 | 30 °C, 1–2 M |",
