        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "## Prediction for a new polydentate amine ligand\n\n| Oxidation state | Predicted behavior with a new polydentate amine |\n|---|---|\n| Co²⁺ | Should form complexes, but with noticeably lower stability constants and faster ligand exchange; equilibria will be more condition-sensitive and more reversible. |\n| Co³⁺ | Should bind **much more strongly**, especially if the ligand is rigid and can enforce octahedral coordination; expect very large cumulative β values and substantial kinetic inertness once formed. |\n\nSo the best prediction is: **a new polydentate amine ligand will strongly prefer Co³⁺ over Co²⁺**, and the preference should increase with **denticity, preorganization/rigidity, and all-nitrogen donor character**. In practice, that means a ligand that gives a modestly stable, labile Co²⁺ complex may give an **exceptionally stable and substitution-inert Co³⁺ complex** after oxidation.",
